# ==============================================================================
# THE JANITOR v5 — DEFINITIVE IGNORE PROTOCOL
# ==============================================================================
# Sections:
#   1. Rust / Cargo
#   2. The Janitor Runtime State
#   3. Security Critical
#   4. AI Assistant Instructions
#   5. Documentation Build
#   6. Python (gauntlet testing)
#   7. Compiled Objects & Binaries
#   8. IDE & Editor
#   9. Operating System
#  10. Logs & Diagnostics
#  11. Tree-sitter / C grammar generated files
#  12. Node.js (optional tooling)
# ==============================================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. RUST / CARGO
# Cargo build artifacts. Cargo.lock IS tracked (binary crate = reproducible builds).
# Per-crate /target entries in crates/*/gitignore are redundant but harmless.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
/target/
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. THE JANITOR RUNTIME STATE
# Everything under .janitor/ is machine-local runtime state:
#   ghost/          — backup copies of physically deleted symbols
#   shadow_src/     — symlink overlay (Shadow Tree)
#   symbols.rkyv    — rkyv registry cache (regenerated by `janitor scan`)
#   symbols.db      — legacy SQLite artifact (replaced by rkyv)
#   audit.json      — append-only deletion audit log
#   kill_list.ld    — ephemeral pipeline intermediate
#   badge.svg       — generated by `janitor badge`
# None of these belong in source control.
# rkyv files anywhere in the workspace are binary runtime data.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.janitor/
*.rkyv


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. SECURITY CRITICAL — NEVER COMMIT
# Private signing keys, HSM tokens, TLS certificates, environment secrets.
# A single accidental commit of a private key invalidates the Vault entirely.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.key
*.pem
*.pem.enc
*.pqc_secret
*.p12
*.pfx
*.token
*.seed
# Belt-and-suspenders explicit entries (also covered by *.key / *.json patterns above).
governor.key
credentials.json
secrets/
/crates/vault/secrets/
/crates/common/attestations/local/
attestations/local/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. AI ASSISTANT INSTRUCTIONS
# CLAUDE.md contains internal architecture directives, supply-chain SHAs, and
# operational guidance for AI coding assistants. It is a local working document
# and must not be committed to the public repository.
# .claude/ is the Claude Code local state directory.
# .agent/ is reserved for any future agentic runtime state.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
.agent/


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. DOCUMENTATION BUILD
# `mkdocs build` and `mkdocs gh-deploy` generate the `site/` directory.
# The build output is ephemeral — only the source docs/ are tracked.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
site/


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. PYTHON (gauntlet testing / ecosystem tooling)
# The gauntlet runs pytest against Python library repos. Python cache artifacts
# must not pollute the workspace.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.venv/
venv/
env/
.python-version
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
htmlcov/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.tox/
*.egg


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. COMPILED OBJECTS & FOREIGN BINARIES
# Object files, LLVM bitcode, and shared libraries generated during build.
# Windows executables in the repo root are NOT tracked (gh.exe lives at a
# system path on the Windows host, not in the workspace).
# Exception: the `janitor` release binary lives in target/release/ (ignored
# by rule 1 above) and is attached to GitHub Releases, not committed.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.o
*.bc
*.so
*.dylib
*.a
*.lib
*.dll
*.exe


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. IDE & EDITOR ARTIFACTS
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml
*.iws
*.ipr
.project
.classpath
.settings/
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.\#*


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. OPERATING SYSTEM
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 10. LOGS & DIAGNOSTICS
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.log.*


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 13. DATABASES & PERSISTENT STATE FILES
# SQLite artefacts from any runtime component (Governor, legacy janitor state).
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db-shm
*.db-wal


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 14. SOCKETS & IPC
# Unix domain sockets created by `janitor serve` and the Governor daemon.
# These are ephemeral; they must never be committed.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.sock


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 15. GOVERNOR / THE JANITOR RUNTIME ARTEFACTS
# /bonds/         — Governor bond state written at runtime.
# /integrity.jsonl — append-only integrity log (runtime, not source).
# Neither belongs in source control.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
/bonds/
/integrity.jsonl


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 11. TREE-SITTER / C GRAMMAR GENERATED FILES
# The `cc` crate compiles tree-sitter grammar `.c` sources at build time.
# Any `parser.c` in the workspace is generated, not authored.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
parser.c


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 12. NODE.JS (optional tooling, not a primary dependency)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm
.yarn/
package-lock.json
